Check out our website-- it's a direct api call to our subnet miners. We have made an un-exploitable mechanism for miners to scrape and index many databases from the internet (twitter, wikipedia, youtube, arvix, etc.)

As soon as you type and enter a query in the search box, it gets immediately sent to the subnet miner which triggers an api request to the relevant database. We have langchain implementation for miners to choose the best option to scrape (or you can choose which options from the start menu). 

We validate and score the miner responses by checking the relevance (usefulness) and validity of the returned links. We additionally require that miners analyze all scraped data and provide an accurate summary for the user. From our website, with live real-time scraping, the twitter links to answer your question are generally posted from within one hour ago!
